 This BlackJack program should run as a Java Applet. 
 It supports muliple players against a dealer using standard rules. 
 It will be able to use a varying number of decks of cards. 
 It will have a set of buttons to place a bet, deal the cards, hit, and stand.  
 The player has 100 chips at beginning, and will be able split pairs if he gets two cards with same number. 
 The dealer will play by standard rules: hit until it reaches 17 or more. 
 The user's cards will be displayed on the bottom of the applet, and the dealer's on the top.
 For specific consideration, it will have a maximum of 4 real players and 8 decks of cards in game. 
 Split function will only be able to use in a "one vs one" game.
